ReflectionTestUtils :

ReflectionTestUtils is a utility class provided by Spring in the org.springframework.test.util package. It's commonly used in unit tests to set or get values of private fields in a class when normal dependency injection (like @Autowired or @Value) doesn't apply â€” especially useful when testing with @Mock and @InjectMocks.

Eg :  ReflectionTestUtils.setField(billerServiceHelper, "paymentPerDayTransactionCount", 1);
       in this paymentPerDayTransactionCount - value fetched from application.properties
	   
for application properties we can use this also	   
	   @TestPropertySource(properties = {
        "appsflyer.events.enabled=true"
})
